Cape Town – Three male drivers – aged between 24 and 31 – have been arrested in the CBD by Law Enforcement auxiliary officers in the CBD for allegedly driving under the influence of alcohol. On Thursday evening, a male driver ran a stop street in Bree Street, narrowly escaping a collision with a Law Enforcement vehicle, the City of Cape Town said. The motorist later tested at 0.85 in a breathalyser test. The driver was arrested for driving under the influence  of alcohol and an additional charge of reckless and negligent driving. Shortly after 1am on Friday, officers witnessed a motor vehicle accident on the corner of Buitengracht and Wale streets. One of the drivers was arrested for driving under the influence of alcohol as well as reckless and negligent driving. It was later confirmed he had no driving licence. The third driver was arrested in Bloem Street after initially being warned by officers not to drive his vehicle. He chose to ignore their advice and was promptly arrested. Cape Times